Female terminalia.
Gonocoxite small, very slender; weakly sclerotised; evenly tapered apicad; with short sized stylus (
Fig 1K
). Stylus at apex with tuft of 2–4 setae, apical part of body of gonocoxite also with 4–8 fine and long, laterally prominent setae. Sternite VIII with long, very curved and slender apodeme, 5–6× as long as plate, terminating just at base of plate, creating short basal margin. Plate of sternite VIII sub-isosceles trapezoid shaped; with longitudinally developed arms; and with apical margin badly defined, armed with sparse fringe of setae (
Figs 176–218
). Spermatheca weakly to very weakly sclerotized, small, slender; with very slender cornu and small corpus; the ramus and nodulus not often differing between species; ramus usually slightly longer than wide and nodulus smaller, hump-shaped (
Figs 133–175
).
